goals.1: Identify the BGP to retrieve E.U. countries and their politicians
goals.2: Identify the BGP for obtaining other occupations and properties of politicians
goals.3: How many politicians are recorder for each E.U. country?
goals.4: Are there politicians with double citizenship?
goals.5: Analyze the number of politicians in each country by occupation, for instance
goals.5.1: What are the top-3 occupations for a politician in Italy and France?
goals.5.2: What if you consider only politicians for which we don't have a date of death?
goals.5.3: Which politicians had a spouse that was also a politician? How many in each country?

search_workflow.narrative:
Q1
try to find the property to connect country and EU
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pname WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279 wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country ?p wd:Q46. ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname . } LIMIT 100

search_workflow.narrative:
Q2
try to find the property to connect country and EU
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?o ?oname WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279 wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P361 ?o. ?o <http://schema.org/name> ?oname . } LIMIT 100
output: Allies of the First World War
Allies of the Second World War
South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation

search_workflow.narrative:
Q3
try to find the property to connect country and EU
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?o ?oname WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279 wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P361 ?o; wdt:P30 wd:Q46. ?o <http://schema.org/name> ?oname . } LIMIT 100
output: Allies of the First World War

search_workflow.narrative:
Q4
?s wdt:P361 wd:Q458 BGP for country belonging to EU
count countries in EU
search_workflow.query: SELECT COUNT(?country) WHERE { ?country wdt:P361 wd:Q458. } LIMIT 100

search_workflow.narrative:
Q5
count how many politicians have each country in the EU
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?country (COUNT(?pol) AS ?howMany) WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279 wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P361 wd:Q458. } GROUP BY ?country LIMIT 100

search_workflow.narrative:
Q6
as previous one but with Europe instead EU
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?country (COUNT(DISTINCT ?pol) AS ?howMany) WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279 wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P30 wd:Q46. } GROUP BY ?country ORDER BY DESC(?howMany) LIMIT 100

search_workflow.narrative:
Q7
using Europe instead of EU the results are very different, check why
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?cname WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279 wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country. ?country wdt:P30 wd:Q46. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P361 wd:Q458} ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?cname . } LIMIT 100
output: Crown of the Kingdom of Poland
United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland

search_workflow.narrative: TASK 1 ENDS HERE: BGP to retrieve an EU country and its politicians
search_workflow.query: SELECT ?country ?pol WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country. wd:Q458 wdt:P527 ?country. } LIMIT 10

2.narrative:
Q14
retrieve some predicates of italian politicians
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pname WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 wd:Q38; ?p ?o. FILTER(!isLiteral(?o)) ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname . } LIMIT 100
output: on focus list of Wikimedia project
second family name in Spanish name

2.narrative:
Q15
interesting properties: occupation (P106), member of political party (P102), political ideology (P1142), employer (P108), field of work (P101)
2.query: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ?pol) WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 wd:Q38; wdt:P106 ?occ. } LIMIT 25

2.narrative:
Q16
exclude from result set the ones related to politics
2.query: SELECT ?occ ?name ?howMany WHERE { {SELECT ?occ (COUNT(?pol) AS ?howMany) WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 wd:Q38; wdt:P106 ?occ. FILTER(?occ!=wd:Q82955) } GROUP BY ?occ } ?occ <http://schema.org/name> ?name . } ORDER BY DESC(?howMany) LIMIT 25

2.narrative:
Q17
as before but consider all countries in EU
2.query: SELECT ?occ ?name ?howMany WHERE { {SELECT ?occ (COUNT(?pol) AS ?howMany) WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country; wdt:P106 ?occ. wd:Q458 wdt:P527 ?country. FILTER(?occ!=wd:Q82955) } GROUP BY ?occ } ?occ <http://schema.org/name> ?name . } ORDER BY DESC(?howMany) LIMIT 25

2.narrative:
Q18
most common political ideology (P1142) in italy
2.query: SELECT ?id (COUNT(?pol) AS ?howMany) WHERE{ ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 wd:Q38; wdt:P1142 ?id. } GROUP BY ?id ORDER BY DESC(?howMany) LIMIT 10

2.narrative:
Q19
check if there are more results using member of political party (P102)
2.query: SELECT ?id ?name ?howMany WHERE { {SELECT ?id (COUNT(?pol) AS ?howMany) WHERE{ ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 wd:Q38; wdt:P102 ?id. }} ?id <http://schema.org/name> ?name . } GROUP BY ?id ORDER BY DESC(?howMany) LIMIT 10

2.narrative:
Q20
check predicates of political party (P102)
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pname WHERE { ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 wd:Q38; wdt:P102 ?id. ?id ?p ?o. FILTER(!isLiteral(?o)) ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname . } LIMIT 10

2.narrative:
Q21
Q18 using the new path discovered above (politician->party->ideology)
2.query: SELECT ?id ?name ?howMany WHERE{ {SELECT ?id (COUNT(?pol) AS ?howMany) WHERE{ ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 wd:Q38; wdt:P102 ?party. ?party wdt:P1142 ?id. } GROUP BY ?id} ?id <http://schema.org/name> ?name . } ORDER BY DESC(?howMany) LIMIT 10

2.narrative:
Q22
most common political ideology in EU (per country)
2.query: SELECT ?id ?name ?country ?cname ?howMany WHERE{ {SELECT ?id ?country (COUNT(?pol) AS ?howMany) WHERE{ ?pol wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q82955; wdt:P27 ?country; wdt:P102 ?party. ?party wdt:P1142 ?id. wd:Q458 wdt:P527 ?country. } GROUP BY ?id ?country} ?id <http://schema.org/name> ?name . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?cname . } ORDER BY DESC(?howMany) LIMIT 10
